<%@ Page Title="Tips-For-Learning-Spanish-Over-Skype" Language="C#" MasterPageFile="~/MasterPages/RentALanguageTeacher.Master" AutoEventWireup="true" CodeBehind="SkypeTips.aspx.cs" Inherits="RentALanguageTeacher.Pages.Articles.SkypeTips" %>

<asp:Content ID="Content1" ContentPlaceHolderID="HeadContent" runat="server">



</asp:Content>

<asp:Content ID="Content2" ContentPlaceHolderID="cpMainContent" runat="server">

    <div class="ContentSection">
        
        <div class="ContentSectionHeader"><div class="ContentSectionHeaderText"><%: Page.Title %></div></div>
        
        <div class="ContentSectionContent">

            <div class="Content">

                <div class="ContentTitleImage"><a href="/Home"><img src="/Images/LogoBlack.png" class="center" /></a></div>
                
                <div class="ContentTitletext">

                    <p>Learning Spanish or any foreign language over Skype can be difficult.  To help put you at ease and 
                        make you learning experience the best, we have a few tips for you. While we cannot guarantee that 
                        following these tips will make you fluent in one class, it will surely help you get there with time.</p>

                </div>

            </div>

        </div>

    </div>

    <div class="ContentSection">
        
        <div class="ContentSectionHeader"><div class="ContentSectionHeaderText">Have enough light in the room, and on your face</div></div>
        
        <div class="ContentSectionContent">

            <div class="Content">

                 <div class="ContentTitleImage"><a href="/Home"><img src="/Images/Liststeps/1.png" class="center" /></a></div>
                
                <div class="ContentTitletext">

                    <p>Having a well lit room with light shining towards your face will make the picture as clear as possible.  
                    Having a clear picture with all your facial features shown can help you and your teacher communicate.  
                    Watching facial expressions and lip movement is a big part of language learning, and with a properly 
                    lit room and Skype it will be as if you really were sitting in front of each other.  
                </p>

                </div>

                

            </div>

        </div>

    </div>

    <div class="ContentSection">
        
        <div class="ContentSectionHeader"><div class="ContentSectionHeaderText">Pick a quiet, comfortable space</div></div>
        
        <div class="ContentSectionContent">

            <div class="Content">

                <div class="ContentTitleImage"><a href="/Home"><img src="/Images/Liststeps/2.png" class="center" /></a></div>
                
                <div class="ContentTitletext">

                    <p>Picking a quiet space will give you the best audio quality for both talking and listening. Choosing a 
                    room with not too big and with a few obstacles and furniture will keep echoes down and let you and 
                    your teacher talk in a comfortable manner. Rent a Language Teacher suggests a comfy couch or bed, 
                    where you can be comfortable sitting up, and keep your voice for competing with other noises.  
                </p>

                </div>

                

            </div>

        </div>

    </div>

        <div class="ContentSection">
        
        <div class="ContentSectionHeader"><div class="ContentSectionHeaderText">Ask to repeat words as often as necessary</div></div>
        
        <div class="ContentSectionContent">

            <div class="Content">

                 <div class="ContentTitleImage"><a href="/Home"><img src="../../Images/Liststeps/3.png" class="center" /></a></div>
                
                <div class="ContentTitletext">

                    <p>Spend time repeating them especially if you did not hear correctly.  
                        In Spanish they say no tengas pena, or don’t be afraid to ask again and again, repetition is the key!
                </p>

                </div>

                

            </div>

        </div>

    </div>

    <div class="ContentSection">
        
        <div class="ContentSectionHeader"><div class="ContentSectionHeaderText">Use a headset with a microphone</div></div>
        
        <div class="ContentSectionContent">

            <div class="Content">

                <div class="ContentTitleImage"><a href="/Home"><img src="../../Images/Liststeps/4.png" class="center" /></a></div>
                
                <div class="ContentTitletext">

                    <p>Using a headset will increase your audio quality and keep your hands free for communication via body language and taking notes.
                </p>

                </div>

                

            </div>

        </div>

    </div>

    <div class="ContentSection">
        
        <div class="ContentSectionHeader"><div class="ContentSectionHeaderText">Use Screen Sharing as a language learning tool</div></div>
        
        <div class="ContentSectionContent">

            <div class="Content">

                 <div class="ContentTitleImage"><a href="/Home"><img src="/Images/Liststeps/5.png" class="center" /></a></div>
                
                <div class="ContentTitletext">

                    <p>Sharing your screen can let you and your teacher look at the same thing at the same time.  
                        You can use the cursor as a pointer and highlight unknown words and follow along.  Use these digital tools as much as possible!
                </p>

                </div>

                

            </div>

        </div>

    </div>

    <div class="ContentSection">
        
        <div class="ContentSectionHeader"><div class="ContentSectionHeaderText">Keep Skype up to date</div></div>
        
        <div class="ContentSectionContent">

            <div class="Content">

                <div class="ContentTitleImage"><a href="/Home"><img src="/Images/Liststeps/6.png" class="center" /></a></div>
                
                <div class="ContentTitletext">

                    <p>Keeping Skype up to date is essential as they are always making improvements and adding new features.
                </p>

                </div>

                

            </div>

        </div>

    </div>

    <div class="ContentSection">
        
        <div class="ContentSectionHeader"><div class="ContentSectionHeaderText">Close all other programs</div></div>
        
        <div class="ContentSectionContent">

            <div class="Content">

                 <div class="ContentTitleImage"><a href="/Home"><img src="/Images/Liststeps/7.png" class="center" /></a></div>
                
                <div class="ContentTitletext">

                    <p>With all your other programs closed Skype can use all your computers resources and run a t full speed.  
                        This will ensure you and your teacher can have a smooth class without any interruptions.
                </p>

                </div>

                

            </div>

        </div>

    </div>

    <div class="ContentSection">
        
        <div class="ContentSectionHeader"><div class="ContentSectionHeaderText">Use notes</div></div>
        
        <div class="ContentSectionContent">

            <div class="Content">

                <div class="ContentTitleImage"><a href="/Home"><img src="/Images/Liststeps/8.png" class="center" /></a></div>
                
                <div class="ContentTitletext">

                    <p>Just because the class room has gone 21 century with technology doesn’t mean you can’t take good old fashioned notes. 
                </p>

                </div>

                

            </div>

        </div>

    </div>

    <div class="ContentSection">
        
        <div class="ContentSectionHeader"><div class="ContentSectionHeaderText">Have a dictionary handy</div></div>
        
        <div class="ContentSectionContent">

            <div class="Content">

                 <div class="ContentTitleImage"><a href="/Home"><img src="/Images/Liststeps/9.png" class="center" /></a></div>
                
                <div class="ContentTitletext">

                    <p>Whether it’s an online dictionary or translator, or a hard copy, keep it handy so you can look up new words as you need them
                </p>

                </div>

                

            </div>

        </div>

    </div>

</asp:Content>
